@page "/"

<PageTitle>InsTK Workstation</PageTitle>

<div class="home-page">
    <section class="home-hero">
        <p class="home-eyebrow">Instructor workstation</p>
        <h1>InsTK</h1>
        <p class="home-description">
            InsTK is a Windows-first workstation app for local grading workflows, managed Ollama model execution,
            and backend-connected instructor tooling.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="home-grid">
        <article class="home-card">
            <h2>Settings</h2>
            <p>Configure the backend URL, managed Ollama runtime, model selection, and workstation policy.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="home-card">
            <h2>Ollama</h2>
            <p>Run prompts against the local Ollama endpoint and see whether each response came from the primary or fallback model.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="home-card">
            <h2>Brightspace</h2>
            <p>Log into Brightspace locally with Playwright, save the workstation session, and discover available courses without routing student data through the server.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="home-card">
            <h2>Machine-Aware Setup</h2>
            <p>The app profiles current memory availability and recommends curated Ollama models that fit the workstation.</p>
        </article>
    </section>
</div>
